    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What should I do immediately when my roof starts leaking?</h3>
      <p>Contain the water with buckets and towels. Move electronics and valuables out of the wet area. Take photos before cleaning up. Then call a licensed roofing contractor immediately — don't wait to see if the leak stops on its own.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Does homeowners insurance cover emergency roof leak repair in Utah?</h3>
      <p>If the leak is caused by a storm, falling tree, or other sudden event, most Utah homeowners insurance policies will cover it. Gradual wear or maintenance neglect is typically excluded. Document everything and call your insurer promptly after engaging a contractor.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can a roofer put a tarp on my roof the same day?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Emergency tarping is available throughout Salt Lake County. A waterproof tarp is secured over the damaged section to stop water intrusion while a permanent repair is arranged — often within the same week.</p>
    </div>

